Preheat your #oven{} to 200 degrees. Remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and @yellow pepper{1} and cut into slices about 2cm wide. Peel and chop the @red onion{1} into roughly 3cm pieces. Peel the @carrot{2} and remove the top and bottom, then cut in half lengthways. Next chop those lengths into batons roughly the length of your little finger.

Put your pepper, carrot and onion on a #baking tray{}. Mix together a splash of @oil{splash}, the @Caribbean style jerk sauce{1.5} and the @mango chutney{1} in a #bowl{} and drizzle this over your veggies.

> The jerk sauce can be a little spicy, so just add half if you're not a spice fan.

Add a @salt{pinch} and a good grind of @black pepper{grind} to the tray, give it a good shake until everything is well coated. Prick each @spiced pork sausage{4} with a #sharp knife{} (twice per sausage) and pop on top of your veggies.

Pop your baking tray on the top shelf of your oven for ~{25-30%minutes}. Halfway through cooking, give the baking tray a shake and put it back in your oven.

In the meantime, bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil with a @salt{pinch}. Peel and chop the @potato{1} into roughly 2cm pieces and add to your boiling water. Cook for ~{10%minutes} until soft.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

While your potato is cooking, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}.

Once your potato is cooked, drain, return to the #pot{} and add a small knob of @?butter{small knob} (if you have some), a splash of @?milk{splash} (if you have it), a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @black pepper{grind}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until you have a smooth consistency.

> If the potato is cooked before the sausages and veggies, simply put a lid on the pot until everything else is ready.

When your sausage is browned and your veggies are cooked, get your baking tray out of your oven and stir your parsley through your veggies.

> The sausage is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Serve your mash with your sausage on the side, your veggies piled on top and a sprinkling of parsley to finish. Enjoy!